&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location –   Cantilupe ward, Stonebow Unit&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Registered Mental Health Nurse (RMN)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;BAND 5&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;37.5 HOURS PER WEEK&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; An opportunity has arisen for a full time staff nurse post on Cantilupe Ward  at the Stonebow Unit.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Cantilupe is a 10 bed ward for older adults with organic illness – predominantly dementia with features of Behavioural and Psychiatric Symptoms of Dementia.  Our patients often have complex physical health needs and the successful candidate will demonstrate a passion for a holistic approach to meeting the care needs of the patients. We work closely with allied health professionals within the Unit and our aim is to maximise the health and well being of the patients in our care and support them and their families.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Cantilupe ward delivers End of Life Care and have strong links with the County Hospital palliative care team and  St Michaels Hospice .&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; We are looking to appoint motivated and dynamic individuals to join our Multi-disciplinary team. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Cantilupe has a supportive and motivated team of staff and being part of that team would allow you the opportunity to develop a broad repertoire of skills to support people who are experiencing debilitating   symptoms of dementia but also managing their physical health needs and frailty. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The current shift pattern will involve you working day and night shifts including bank holidays and weekend working. The day shift is 7:30-20:00 hrs and the night shift is 19:30-08:00 hrs&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you require any further information please contact Julie Burchill,  Ward Manager on Cantilupe directly on 01432-364047&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Flexible working arrangements will be considered. Any request will be set against genuine operational requirements and limitations and it is not obligatory for a manager to accede to the request. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Trust reserves the right to close this vacancy when sufficient applications have been received.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
